item.title: World leaders launch WHO COVID-19 plan
item.description: French President Emmanuel Macron and German Chancellor Angela Merkel will help launch a global initiative to accelerate work to fight COVID-19, the World Health Organisation says, but the United States says it will not take part.

item.title: Spain reports more recovered than infected
item.description: Spanish health authorities are reporting that, for the first time since the beginning of the coronavirus outbreak there, more people are being diagnosed as cured than those falling sick.

item.title: Trump virus disinfectant comments slammed
item.description: Doctors and health experts urged people not to drink or inject disinfectant after US President Donald Trump suggested scientists should investigate inserting the cleaning agent into the body as a way to cure COVID-19.

item.title: Perth airport seizes Virgin aircraft
item.description: Perth Airport has seized a number of parked Virgin Australia aircraft because of unpaid invoices, with the airport saying it must "protect its own interests".

item.title: Social distancing not needed in classrooms
item.description: The Morrison government continues to mount pressure on the states to return schools to normal as soon as possible, as progress is made on tackling the coronavirus.

item.title: Three dead, 13 injured in Vietnam storm
item.description: Three people have been killed and 13 injured as a thunderstorm passed over several mountainous provinces in northern Vietnam.

item.title: Ninth Tas virus death, lockdown extended
item.description: An elderly woman has become the ninth coronavirus death in Tasmania, as authorities extend the state's northwest lockdown to mitigate an outbreak.

item.title: Meghan court case against UK paper begins
item.description: The first court hearing in a privacy case brought by Meghan, Britain's Duchess of Sussex, against a tabloid newspaper for printing part of a letter to her father has begun at London's High Court.

item.title: Fifth virus death at NSW aged care home
item.description: A fifth resident has died after testing positive to COVID-19 at a western Sydney nursing home where more than 40 people have been diagnosed with the virus.

item.title: Almost 1m businesses want JobKeeper pay
item.description: Around 900,000 businesses have indicated they want a share of the federal government's historic $130 billion JobKeeper payment to cushion the impact of coronavirus.
